<subSubSection id="C33EC4D1754AD70E8066F80D5507F71D" pageId="5" pageNumber="385" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8B9B975A754AD70E8066F80D5507F71D" blockId="5.[1402,2610,1663,2248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis id="B9504B48754AD70E8066F80D54A6F7BE" bold="true" box="[1404,1752,2018,2051]" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The 
<collectingCountry id="F333D7CA754AD70E8CC1F80D57ADF797" name="Madagascar" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
Slit-faced Bat is known only from two individuals captured in June 1910 at the type locality, and it has not been recorded since. Given its restricted known distribution and the fact that 
<collectingCountry id="F333D7CA754AD70E83ABF7B75529F7C4" box="[1713,1879,2136,2169]" name="Madagascar" pageId="5" pageNumber="385">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
has been relatively well surveyed for bats,it is likely either extinct or highly endangered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
